Synthesis of DPA-TPE-Cage.  TPE-Cage (100 mg, 0.081 mmol), DPA (90 ¦ÌL, 0.486 mmol) and K2CO 3 (67 mg, 0.486 mmol) were added to a 50 mL round bottom  flask, and then THF (20 mL) was added. The reaction mixture was stirred for 24 h at 70 ¡æ. After  the raw materials was consumed,  the residue was filtered and purified  by S4column chromatography (dichloromethane/methanol,  8/1) to afford DPA-TPE-Cage as white solid  (134 mg, 81%). 1H NMR (600 MHz, CDCl 3) ¦Ä (ppm) = 8.57 (s, 8 H), 7.67 (m, 8 H), 7.35- 7.34(d, J = 7.8 Hz, 8 H), 7.21 (m, 16 H), 7.06- 7.04(d, J = 7.2 Hz, 4 H), 6.87- 6.85 (d, J = 7.8 Hz, 4 H), 6.80 (m, 8 H), 6.72- 6.71(d, J = 7.8 Hz, 4 H), 6.58-  6.57 (d, J = 7.8 Hz, 4 H), 5.20 (m, 8 H), 5.09 (m, 8 H). 13C NMR (150 MHz, CDCl 3) ¦Ä (ppm) = 171.33,  169.18, 156.73, 150.43, 149.85, 149.37, 140.29, 140.07, 138.81, 136.75, 132.73, 132.33,  129.92, 123.72, 122.38, 121.98, 121.77, 120.75, 119.71, 51.84.

Synthesis of ZnDPA-TPE-Cage. DPA-TPE-Cage  (50 mg, 0.0265 mmol)  was dissolved in chloroform (5 mL) to a 25 mL round  bottom  flask,  anhydrous ZnCl 2 (21.67 mg, 0.159  mmol) was dissolved  in methanol (10 mL) and dropwise to the flask. The reaction mixture  was stirred  for 24 h at 65 ¡æ. After that white precipitate was generated, filtered  to afford ZnDPA-TPE-Cage as white solid  (55 mg, 85%). 1H NMR (600 MHz,  DMSO) ¦Ä (ppm) = 8.55 (s, 8 H), 7.80 (s, 8 H), 7.34 (d, J = 23.2 Hz, 16H),  7.21 - 7.00 (m, 16 H), 6.92 - 6.76 (m, 16 H), 6.68 (d, J = 7.2 Hz, 4 H), 6.51 (d, J = 9.3 Hz, 4 H), 5.16 -  5.01 (m, 8 H), 5.01 - 4.87 (m, 8 H).
